text: Ottavio Cinquanta (15 August 1938 – 18 July 2022) was an Italian sports administrator. He was born in Rome, Italy. He was the President of the International Skating Union from 1994 to 2016. He also was a member of the International Olympic Committee from 1996 to 2008.
